  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Accepted, W-CON-01)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors have been reviewed; the assessment team concluded that evidence across verification, validation, and uncertainty quantification activities is collectively sufficient to support an Accepted decision. One factor — model form — was evaluated through a structured expert elicitation and qualitative engineering judgment process rather than a graduated level assignment, consistent with the team's interpretation of ASME V&V 40 for high-fidelity turbulence model selection at MRL 5.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-hemolysis-cfd-acceptable",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-measurements",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-bench-5operating-points",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-ensemble"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
